      <notesStmt>
        <note>Title from colophon and cover page (f. 1r). Cover page reads: Sumukhatatvacandrikā pustakam idaṁ śrībhavadevabhaṭṭānām.</note>
        <note>The author, Jayakṛṣṇa Brahmamuni, is the pupil of Sureśvarānandatīrtha (see colophon).</note>
        <note>Written 12-16 lines per leaf by multiple scribes. Ff. 7-10 poorly written.</note>
        <note>Fair condition. Leaves brown, slightly brittle, and fraying at edges. Ink fading on several leaves. Mistakes blotched out with black or crossed through. Ff. 1-6 have orange powder highlighting section divisions, invocations and colophons.</note>
        <note>Text begins (f. 1v): om̐ śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ. yat smṛtvā viṣṇurudrādyāsvasvakāryāṇyasādhayan. tatsaccitmukhavighneśabrahmāsmyakriyam advayam (verse 1). brahmavidyārthi[-]emegre gurubhiḥ śrāvito[hy?]aham śuklāṁvaradharaśloka soyaṁ matyai vicāryate (verse 2). śuklāṁvaradharaviṣṇuṁ śaśivarṇaṁ caturbhujaṁ [ ]vadanaṁ dhyāyet sarvavighnopaśāntaye (verse 3).</note>
        <note>Text ends (f. 10v): om̐ tat sat śrīpārvatīparameśvaravighneśvarebhyo namaḥ. kvāhaṁ kva granthakaraṇaṁ kiṁ tu yeṣām prasādajñaḥ muktasyāṁ śrīguruśrīśavedāntāste girārcit[ ].</note>
      </notesStmt>
